Last week, Vestas Wind Systems in conjucntion with the Danish Embassy, held a cocktail reception at the ambassador&rsquo;s residence in Muthaiga, Nairobi.The event was celebrating the Lake Turkana wind power project half time installation milestone. Supplying 365 wind turbines with acapacity of 850 kW each, the project covers 162 km2 and will provide approximately 18 per cent of Kenya&rsquo;s current installed electricity generating capacity.In attendance were Energy &amp; Petroleum PS Eng Joseph Njoroge, Dannish ambassador Mette Knudsen, Lake Turkana Wind Power deputy general manager Caroline Ongeri and Kenya Climate Innovation chief executive Edward Mungai.